    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                <head>No. 16.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Osborn</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 14,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 22.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 13, of the 10th
                        ultimo, and am much pleased to see the evidence of the good will borne by
                        Brazil to the United States which is contained in the imperial government’s
                        prompt acceptance of the invitation to send representatives to an American
                        Congress in November next.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
